tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant dyslipidemia (elevated total cholesterol, LDL, triglycerides, and low HDL), and mildly elevated fasting glucose, suggesting increased cardiovascular and metabolic risk. Renal function and electrolytes are within normal limits, and there is no evidence of microalbuminuria. Continued monitoring and management of lipid and glucose levels are recommended.
